Welcome to Asakusa, Tokyo
Asakusa is one of Tokyo's most famous and historic districts. It is known for its traditional
atmosphere, beautiful temples, and lively shopping streets.
Main Attractions
● Senso-ji Temple: Tokyo's oldest temple, featuring the iconic Kaminarimon (Thunder
Gate) and a bustling approach.
● Nakamise-dori: A street leading to the temple, filled with shops selling traditional snacks,
crafts, and souvenirs.
● Sumida Park: A beautiful spot along the Sumida River, perfect for cherry blossom
viewing and river cruises.
Tips for Visitors
Activity Recommendation
Shopping Try local street snacks like Ningyo-yaki.
Sightseeing Visit the temple early in the morning to avoid
crowds.
Getting There
Asakusa is easily accessible via the Ginza Subway Line, Asakusa Line, and Tobu Railways.
